cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

The paper deals with the problem of optimal control of continuous-time systems using Q-learning, which is a popular reinforcement learning technique. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the modeling, analysis, and control of dynamical systems. The paper also proposes two Q-learning algorithms, which involve machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of Q-functions, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also involves the use of value iteration, which is a common technique in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of computer simulations to verify the effectiveness of the proposed algorithms, making cs.RO (Robotics) another possible category.
